<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1903-08-15T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1903-08-15T00:00:00-05:00" n="76" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d76">
                        <head><hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Hay</persName> to Mr.
                                    <persName type="to">Conger</persName>.</hi></head>
                        <opener><seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.—Paraphrase.]</seg></opener>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>,<lb/><hi rend="italic">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1903-08-15"><hi rend="italic">August 15,
                                1903</hi></date>.</dateline></opener>
                        <p>Acknowledging Mr. Conger’s telegram of August 14, Mr. Hay states that
                            Prince Ch’ing’s note is satisfactory; that the date for signing of
                            completed treaty, October 8, is absolute and not contingent on action of
                            Russia. Mr. Conger is directed to make this clear to Prince Ch’ing.)</p>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>